mkdir-> makes directory 
mkdir dir-> for single directory 
mkdir dir/dir1/dir2->for multiple directory 
mkdir folder{1..10}-> create folder 1 to 10.
rmdir folder{1..10}->remove folder created from 1 to 10
cat filename-> used to read contents in a file
date +%D-> see date in mm/dd/yy format
date +%t-> see date in time format
put . front of a file to create a hidden file
cat >filename-> used to create a file using cat command
cat filename->read all the text in a file.
cat >>filename-> to append the file
mv .hidden1.txt hidden1.txt->convert hidden file to normal file.

